ContactSign UpFounded in Fargo.Where we startedFounded from a university engineering product aiming to design a 3D printed myoelectric arm, Protosthetics quickly realized that O&P was more excited about getting the benefits of 3D printing for existing products than looking for something new.With that in mind, we launched our central fabrication business in 2016, and have been continuously combining the best customer experience, clinical knowledge, and cutting edge fabrication techniques. Protosthetics brings products to O&P clinicians that allow them to best fulfill their primary purpose - providing excellent patient care to those that deserve it most. A leader in additive manufacturing.how we got here3DÂ printing started as a means to more reliably and cost effectively create products that already exist in O&P. After innovating in manufacturing the current standard of care products using this transformative technology, we've worked to design new ones across the O&P landscape. âAfter years of customer requests for the benefits of 3D printing in-clinic - improved turnaround time, savings, and repeatability - we launched the Galileo program in late 2021. It's the first of its kind, a fully managed 3D printing program designed exclusively for O&P, built from the ground up with the practitioner in mind. Cutting edge tech, backed by people who care.where we're goingAt Protosthetics, our North Star is a stellar customer experience. Providing 3D printed prosthetics had always been on Deckerâs radar as a solution, but he didn't dive for it until Galileo came along.âDecker with the Protosthetics Galileo Printer and 3D Printed SocketsâIn November, 2022, Decker implemented 3D printing at Sandhills by introducing the Galileo program, and his team completely embraced the new process with proof of efficiency. Decker sees Galileo as another technical team on his side. âTheyâre just a text away, a phone call away, and are always so receptive.âÂ âWith the 3D printer on-site, Decker and his team can rapidly turn ideas into reality and gain control over their work.
